2.91mln residents affected as torrential rains hit Hunan 
2012-05-15 09:58:50 GMT
Torrential rain that struck south China since May 11 has affected the daily lives of 2.91 million residents within Hunan as of Monday noon. Direct economic losses caused by the flood reached 2.88 billion yuan (456.2 million U.S. dollars), according to provincial flood control authorities.
